narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course would be enjoyable to any student with an interest in art or philosophy, and the course is designed in a way that allows students with a variety of academic backgrounds to participate meaningfully.

I would absolutely recommend the class. The subject matter is engaging and Professor Gilmore is exceedingly interesting to listen to and does not expect perfection, which makes for a very satisfying seminar experience.
Very good seminar, with a very intensive reading load. Your entire grade is decided by one essay, also.
If you can take this class, do it.
